--- Part 10: MASTER CONNECTION ---

  THEOREM (conjectured): For odd n, the alternating simplex
  inscribed in [0,1]^n has volume 1/(n+1).

  Therefore: cube/simplex ratio = n+1 = det(A_n) = Cartan det.

  CONNECTION TO TOURNAMENTS:
  • key₁ = 2 = cube/simplex ratio at n=2
  • key₂ = 3 = cube/simplex ratio at n=3
  • I(Ω, key₁) = H(T) = Hamiltonian paths
  • The k-nacci root → 2 = key₁
  • The weighted k-nacci root → 3 = key₂

  INTERPRETATION: The OCF says H = I(Ω, 2).
  The '2' comes from the simplex-in-cube packing ratio at n=2.
  The independence polynomial evaluated at the packing ratio
  counts Hamiltonian paths!

  What does I(Ω, 3) count?
  For k disjoint 3-cycles: I(Ω,3) = 4^k
  For k pairwise-intersecting: I(Ω,3) = 1 + 3k
  This should count some '3D packing' of tournaments!

  CONJECTURE: I(Ω, n+1) has a combinatorial interpretation
  as the count of some n-dimensional packing structure
  in the tournament.
